1
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:11,500
[suspenseful music playing]

2
00:00:12,166 --> 00:00:16,041
[Han Chieh] <i>Golden Lake Plaza,</i>
<i>it's the last location of the formation.</i>

3
00:00:16,125 --> 00:00:19,541
[Tien-chi] <i>One last step,</i>
<i>and your daughter is front page news.</i>

4
00:00:19,625 --> 00:00:21,583
[music intensifies]

5
00:00:27,458 --> 00:00:29,500
GOLDEN LAKE PLAZA

6
00:00:29,583 --> 00:00:31,250
[sobbing]

7
00:00:32,875 --> 00:00:34,541
[Han Chieh] Damn you, Tien-chi.

8
00:00:38,208 --> 00:00:40,625
[continues sobbing]

9
00:00:42,208 --> 00:00:45,250
- Yu-ching, I'm coming to see you.
- [music crescendos]

10
00:00:45,333 --> 00:00:46,750
[Han Chieh] Cheng-nan!

11
00:00:46,833 --> 00:00:47,875
[music stops]

12
00:00:48,916 --> 00:00:51,375
Back, stay back! Don't come near me!

13
00:00:51,458 --> 00:00:52,291
Oh.

14
00:00:52,375 --> 00:00:54,791
- Don't come closer.
- Calm down.

15
00:00:55,375 --> 00:00:57,250
Don't be rash. Step down.

16
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:59,666
I'm sick of this world
where evil is the same as good.

17
00:00:59,750 --> 00:01:01,916
The cops are evil as well.

18
00:01:03,166 --> 00:01:05,375
What… What will happen if I jump now?

19
00:01:05,458 --> 00:01:09,125
The whole world will talk about it online,
then the police will take it seriously.

20
00:01:09,208 --> 00:01:10,083
No, listen.

21
00:01:10,166 --> 00:01:12,166
We don't know if the body is Yu-ching.

22
00:01:12,250 --> 00:01:14,958
We'll find the killer soon. Don't do this.

23
00:01:15,541 --> 00:01:17,916
- Come down.
- You stay there!

24
00:01:18,000 --> 00:01:19,500
[tense music playing]

25
00:01:19,583 --> 00:01:21,041
I've killed someone.

26
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:23,041
I killed that little bastard.

27
00:01:23,625 --> 00:01:27,041
- [Chang Min] Chao, he's on the roof.
- [Chao] <i>I've got the DNA report.</i>

28
00:01:27,125 --> 00:01:28,666
<i>That body, it's not Yu-ching.</i>

29
00:01:28,750 --> 00:01:31,083
<i>Yu-ching is alive. Stop him. Stop him now.</i>

30
00:01:31,166 --> 00:01:33,083
- [call disconnects]
- Fuck you, Tien-chi.

31
00:01:33,166 --> 00:01:36,250
That guy didn't die.
Right now, he's in hospital.

32
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:38,041
You didn't kill anyone.

33
00:01:38,125 --> 00:01:40,958
I know you're all lying.
I know you're all lying.

34
00:01:42,250 --> 00:01:44,041
Yu-ching is dead.

35
00:01:44,125 --> 00:01:45,541
I killed someone.

36
00:01:45,625 --> 00:01:46,958
It's too late now.

37
00:01:47,041 --> 00:01:48,333
- It's too late.
- Don't do it!

38
00:01:48,416 --> 00:01:50,416
[music stops]

39
00:01:52,541 --> 00:01:54,541
[breathing heavily]

40
00:01:58,583 --> 00:02:00,625
I wanted to kill myself.

41
00:02:03,458 --> 00:02:04,833
I've been there.

42
00:02:06,208 --> 00:02:08,541
[sad music playing]

43
00:02:08,625 --> 00:02:10,041
If you die,

44
00:02:12,750 --> 00:02:14,333
you'll regret this.

45
00:02:16,916 --> 00:02:17,916
You will.

46
00:02:21,791 --> 00:02:23,791
- Think about your daughter.
- [sobs]

47
00:02:23,875 --> 00:02:26,958
What will she do if you die?

48
00:02:30,708 --> 00:02:32,125
[crying] Yu-ching.

49
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:38,750
[Chang Min] Wait! Wait.

50
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:40,958
Your daughter's alive. I have the report.

51
00:02:41,041 --> 00:02:42,291
It's not your daughter.

52
00:02:43,291 --> 00:02:44,291
Don't jump.

53
00:02:44,375 --> 00:02:45,625
[dramatic music playing]

54
00:02:48,708 --> 00:02:49,750
- Hey!
- [groans]

55
00:03:03,041 --> 00:03:05,041
[music turns eerie]

56
00:03:12,750 --> 00:03:14,750
[phone dialing]

57
00:03:16,916 --> 00:03:21,916
AGENT FROM ABOVE

58
00:03:22,958 --> 00:03:26,958
THE DESCENT

59
00:03:27,458 --> 00:03:29,458
[sirens wailing]0

60
00:03:29,541 --> 00:03:31,541
[action music playing]

61
00:03:41,250 --> 00:03:42,750
[sirens stop]

62
00:03:50,750 --> 00:03:53,500
- Get an ambulance.
- [officer] <i>…located the abductee.</i>

63
00:03:53,583 --> 00:03:56,250
<i>- We need an ambulance.</i>
- <i>All units, abductee located.</i>

64
00:03:56,333 --> 00:03:57,541
Yu-ching.

65
00:03:58,291 --> 00:03:59,375
Yu-ching.

66
00:04:01,083 --> 00:04:03,916
- [music fades]
- [siren wailing]

67
00:04:12,458 --> 00:04:15,041
The man you stabbed
he's going to be all right.

68
00:04:15,125 --> 00:04:18,041
No vital organs are damaged. Mmm.

69
00:04:21,166 --> 00:04:24,041
- [gasps]
- Here. Clean yourself up.

70
00:04:26,916 --> 00:04:28,916
[sobbing joyfully]

71
00:04:29,000 --> 00:04:31,000
[poignant music playing]

72
00:04:47,666 --> 00:04:49,666
[both crying]

73
00:04:51,000 --> 00:04:52,125
Yu-ching.

74
00:05:01,416 --> 00:05:04,041
[Cheng-nan] Don't be afraid.
Don't be afraid.

75
00:05:09,833 --> 00:05:12,333
[both continue sobbing]

76
00:05:23,666 --> 00:05:24,916
[music fades]

77
00:05:25,000 --> 00:05:26,083
Wait there.

78
00:05:28,916 --> 00:05:29,875
Here.

79
00:05:29,958 --> 00:05:31,583
Take this. Okay?

80
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:34,000
[soft music playing]

81
00:05:34,083 --> 00:05:35,291
- You…
- Mmm?

82
00:05:35,375 --> 00:05:37,416
Are you sure you won't come with us?

83
00:05:38,250 --> 00:05:40,375
I want to stay there. Don't worry.

84
00:05:40,458 --> 00:05:44,500
Remember, eat healthy food. Got it?

85
00:05:46,916 --> 00:05:47,750
Oh.

86
00:05:49,375 --> 00:05:51,375
[soft music continues]

87
00:05:53,041 --> 00:05:55,833
- Try hard not to miss me.
- I'll try.

88
00:05:55,916 --> 00:05:57,041
[both chuckle]

89
00:06:19,458 --> 00:06:22,083
[music turns eerie]

90
00:06:29,541 --> 00:06:31,541
[breathing nervously]

91
00:06:34,958 --> 00:06:35,791
[Mr. Lo] Sis.

92
00:06:35,875 --> 00:06:37,416
[poignant music playing]

93
00:06:42,666 --> 00:06:44,916
You've been hiding for so long.

94
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,625
You're showing me your face now?

95
00:06:55,416 --> 00:06:59,833
I didn't show myself
because I hoped you'd eventually move on.

96
00:06:59,916 --> 00:07:00,916
DONGFENG EATERY

97
00:07:02,625 --> 00:07:05,041
I thought after some time

98
00:07:05,583 --> 00:07:06,791
you'd forget about me.

99
00:07:07,708 --> 00:07:11,625
But a few years have passed,
and you still can't let me go.

100
00:07:11,708 --> 00:07:13,708
[poignant music continues]

101
00:07:14,750 --> 00:07:16,083
You're always crying.

102
00:07:16,166 --> 00:07:18,833
And every morning,
you keep chanting my name.

103
00:07:18,916 --> 00:07:20,791
How could anybody take that?

104
00:07:21,291 --> 00:07:22,791
You're so dumb.

105
00:07:22,875 --> 00:07:24,666
I can't forget you.

106
00:07:26,000 --> 00:07:27,291
Big moron.

107
00:07:28,791 --> 00:07:30,958
Well, I've never been that clever.

108
00:07:33,333 --> 00:07:35,416
[sobs]

109
00:07:39,666 --> 00:07:44,250
Sis, I pray every day
that you will come to no harm.

110
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:48,458
You want me to rest in peace,
but I'm too worried about my sister.

111
00:07:50,041 --> 00:07:53,333
Listen to Mr. Han. Leave Dongfeng Market.

112
00:07:55,083 --> 00:07:56,458
I can't leave here.

113
00:07:56,541 --> 00:07:59,000
You're an earthbound spirit.
You'll be lonely.

114
00:07:59,083 --> 00:08:01,416
Well, none of
the neighbor ghosts are going,

115
00:08:01,500 --> 00:08:04,541
and the Third Crown Prince's agent
is protecting me.

116
00:08:04,625 --> 00:08:06,375
Who's going to mess with us?

117
00:08:08,291 --> 00:08:10,875
Then will I see you again soon?

118
00:08:13,208 --> 00:08:15,083
You have to promise me first.

119
00:08:15,583 --> 00:08:16,583
What?

120
00:08:19,583 --> 00:08:21,541
Get used to life without me.

121
00:08:25,041 --> 00:08:27,250
And live a long and happy life.

122
00:08:32,416 --> 00:08:34,208
And don't think too much about me.

123
00:08:34,708 --> 00:08:35,875
Just a little.

124
00:08:36,458 --> 00:08:38,666
[poignant music continues]

125
00:08:41,541 --> 00:08:42,541
And…

126
00:08:43,750 --> 00:08:45,416
if there's still a chance,

127
00:08:47,458 --> 00:08:49,625
then we'll meet again here one day.

128
00:08:57,958 --> 00:08:59,125
Okay.

129
00:09:00,625 --> 00:09:02,375
I'll pack up tomorrow.

130
00:09:14,833 --> 00:09:16,833
[sobbing]

131
00:09:22,333 --> 00:09:23,916
[music fades]

132
00:09:25,583 --> 00:09:27,250
That was so close.

133
00:09:28,916 --> 00:09:31,083
- Mmm. We got lucky.
- [cell phone vibrates]

134
00:09:35,166 --> 00:09:36,333
Go ahead.

135
00:09:38,666 --> 00:09:39,500
Oh.

136
00:09:41,333 --> 00:09:42,166
Yeah?

137
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:46,083
- Got it. Fuck.
- [tense music playing]

138
00:09:46,166 --> 00:09:48,833
A man just jumped off
the same building where we were.

139
00:09:48,916 --> 00:09:51,375
- Apparently, he'd lost all his money.
- [phone buzzes]

140
00:09:51,458 --> 00:09:52,708
Time of death?

141
00:09:52,791 --> 00:09:54,125
About an hour ago.

142
00:09:55,166 --> 00:09:56,250
This is him.

143
00:09:57,416 --> 00:09:59,291
[tense music continues]

144
00:09:59,375 --> 00:10:00,708
GENDER: MALE

145
00:10:02,708 --> 00:10:04,500
The elevator's broken.

146
00:10:05,083 --> 00:10:06,875
What's the point in life?

147
00:10:18,916 --> 00:10:20,916
- [tense music builds]
- [thunder cracking]

148
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:27,958
- He had a backup plan.
- [Chang Min] Fuck.

149
00:10:28,041 --> 00:10:32,041
[Han Chieh] The Demon King's spirit
will be channelled in Tien-chi's body.

150
00:10:32,125 --> 00:10:33,875
[music turns suspenseful]

151
00:11:16,958 --> 00:11:18,958
[suspenseful music continues]

152
00:11:24,041 --> 00:11:25,208
[groaning]

153
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:40,458
[moans]

154
00:11:40,541 --> 00:11:41,958
[music stops]

155
00:11:44,125 --> 00:11:46,125
[dramatic music playing]

156
00:11:48,958 --> 00:11:50,958
[exhales menacingly]

157
00:11:54,166 --> 00:11:57,250
[Demon King of the Sixth Heaven]
<i>I finally made it up here.</i>

158
00:12:00,666 --> 00:12:02,666
[growls]

159
00:12:02,750 --> 00:12:04,750
[dramatic music continues]

160
00:12:08,666 --> 00:12:10,041
Tomorrow.

161
00:12:11,875 --> 00:12:12,875
The battle begins.

162
00:12:15,791 --> 00:12:18,625
[Chang Min] Fuck.
What is this? <i>Stranger Things</i>?

163
00:12:21,125 --> 00:12:22,083
[music fades]

164
00:12:49,416 --> 00:12:51,416
[low tense music playing]

165
00:12:53,583 --> 00:12:55,583
[thunder cracking]

166
00:13:00,958 --> 00:13:02,958
[wind blowing]

167
00:13:07,083 --> 00:13:09,083
[birds chirping]

168
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,250
[Yeh Tzu] Mr. Han.

169
00:13:16,833 --> 00:13:19,666
- Why are you still here?
- The ghosts are still here.

170
00:13:19,750 --> 00:13:22,625
I bought some snacks
for Hsiao-ming and the grannies.

171
00:13:24,125 --> 00:13:26,625
There are weapons I need. You go home.

172
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:29,958
The war is tonight, isn't it?

173
00:13:33,208 --> 00:13:34,291
Yes.

174
00:13:34,375 --> 00:13:36,916
Can I tag along until nightfall?

175
00:13:40,416 --> 00:13:42,708
They're your feet. It's up to you.

176
00:13:42,791 --> 00:13:45,583
There's somewhere
I want to show you later. Will you come?

177
00:13:53,833 --> 00:13:55,833
[thunder rumbling]

178
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:12,416
After I got sick, I'd sometimes come
and have quiet time here.

179
00:14:12,500 --> 00:14:14,500
I'd wish on this tree.

180
00:14:17,458 --> 00:14:19,000
[poignant music playing]

181
00:14:39,541 --> 00:14:40,916
It's a ritual.

182
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:42,875
I say a prayer now.

183
00:14:50,333 --> 00:14:51,291
All done.

184
00:14:53,291 --> 00:14:54,708
What did you wish?

185
00:14:54,791 --> 00:14:56,125
For world peace.

186
00:15:01,125 --> 00:15:03,708
- [Han Chieh] You believe in this?
- Of course.

187
00:15:03,791 --> 00:15:04,791
The old man told me,

188
00:15:04,875 --> 00:15:07,291
"Magic can't defeat spiritual power,

189
00:15:07,375 --> 00:15:11,416
spiritual power can't beat karma,
and karma can't defeat a wish."

190
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:15,166
So a person with a wish
is strongest of all.

191
00:15:15,791 --> 00:15:20,125
You really believe
the world will become peaceful?

192
00:15:20,208 --> 00:15:21,291
It might.

193
00:15:21,791 --> 00:15:25,083
Because in there is all of my love.

194
00:15:25,166 --> 00:15:27,166
[poignant music continues]

195
00:15:28,000 --> 00:15:29,916
[all cheer]

196
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:43,541
Whatever works for you.

197
00:15:44,416 --> 00:15:45,708
You make a wish too.

198
00:15:50,458 --> 00:15:52,833
- No, thanks.
- Come on. Just one.

199
00:15:53,416 --> 00:15:56,125
Hey, make a wish.

200
00:15:56,791 --> 00:15:59,083
- [music fades]
- [thunder rumbles]

201
00:15:59,166 --> 00:16:03,291
TAIPEI CITY POLICE DEPARTMENT
CENTRAL DISTRICT PRECINCT

202
00:16:03,375 --> 00:16:05,375
[tense music playing]

203
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:17,625
[Han Chieh] Come on then.

204
00:16:19,916 --> 00:16:22,250
We should make preparations for tonight.

205
00:16:25,833 --> 00:16:27,583
GOLDEN BRICK

206
00:16:27,666 --> 00:16:29,583
[music intensifies]

207
00:16:58,291 --> 00:17:00,750
DIE AND EAT SHIT,
DEMON KING OF THE SIXTH HEAVEN

208
00:17:02,583 --> 00:17:04,416
Do you think this will really work?

209
00:17:05,291 --> 00:17:07,166
Magical powers can fight ghosts.

210
00:17:08,041 --> 00:17:10,583
Help with this.
There's a lot more to write.

211
00:17:13,291 --> 00:17:15,083
[action music playing]

212
00:17:17,458 --> 00:17:18,333
SUPER PISSED

213
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:39,208
Have you finished over there?

214
00:17:42,416 --> 00:17:43,583
DONGFENG IS THE STRONGEST

215
00:17:43,666 --> 00:17:45,875
THIRD CROWN PRINCE'S
AGENT FROM ABOVE IS HERE

216
00:17:45,958 --> 00:17:47,416
THIRD CROWN PRINCE IS INVINCIBLE

217
00:17:47,500 --> 00:17:48,958
DONGFENG IS THE BEST

218
00:17:49,041 --> 00:17:51,083
CHIEH WILL SURELY TRIUMPH

219
00:17:54,291 --> 00:17:56,833
DEMON KING OF THE SIXTH HEAVEN
AND WU TIEN-CHI, EAT SHIT

220
00:17:57,958 --> 00:17:59,250
[music ends]

221
00:18:21,125 --> 00:18:23,666
[Han Chieh] Fuck.
How will eight be enough?

222
00:18:27,541 --> 00:18:28,625
[Yeh Tzu] Mr. Han?

223
00:18:32,833 --> 00:18:35,291
It's almost time. Go to your home.

224
00:18:35,375 --> 00:18:37,416
Is there anything else I can help with?

225
00:18:39,708 --> 00:18:42,500
Go home and take your medicine.
That will help me.

226
00:18:43,083 --> 00:18:44,083
You know,

227
00:18:45,041 --> 00:18:46,958
if you think the wishing tree's silly,

228
00:18:47,791 --> 00:18:49,750
then ask the Crown Prince for a wish.

229
00:18:52,666 --> 00:18:54,458
[soft music playing]

230
00:18:55,333 --> 00:18:57,416
Ask him to let you win tonight.

231
00:18:58,000 --> 00:18:58,916
Okay?

232
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:05,000
That's up to him entirely.

233
00:19:06,083 --> 00:19:07,416
I never beg.

234
00:19:10,541 --> 00:19:11,500
And…

235
00:19:13,333 --> 00:19:15,208
harboring hope can…

236
00:19:17,083 --> 00:19:18,583
lead to failure.

237
00:19:26,083 --> 00:19:28,083
[music fades]

238
00:19:39,208 --> 00:19:41,208
[Han Chieh] Old man, what are you doing?

239
00:19:41,291 --> 00:19:42,458
Why haven't you gone?

240
00:19:46,875 --> 00:19:48,250
This is my home.

241
00:19:48,333 --> 00:19:50,041
I will always live here.

242
00:19:50,541 --> 00:19:52,708
- Why have you stayed?
- Same reason as you.

243
00:19:52,791 --> 00:19:54,583
But I'm the Crown Prince's agent.

244
00:19:54,666 --> 00:19:58,291
And I'm applying to be
Lord Guan's agent from above.

245
00:19:58,375 --> 00:20:00,333
He's interviewed you for this?

246
00:20:00,416 --> 00:20:02,333
You're not being realistic.

247
00:20:02,416 --> 00:20:04,958
Since the old man is staying,
I'm staying too.

248
00:20:05,041 --> 00:20:06,708
- No, you won't.
- [bangs stick]

249
00:20:07,416 --> 00:20:10,708
You must go. Fighting is for men like us.

250
00:20:12,791 --> 00:20:13,791
[horn honking]

251
00:20:13,875 --> 00:20:15,000
[siren blaring]

252
00:20:15,666 --> 00:20:17,083
[A-Fu] Spareribs.

253
00:20:17,750 --> 00:20:19,166
Pork roll.

254
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:21,250
Spareribs.

255
00:20:21,750 --> 00:20:23,083
Fried chicken.

256
00:20:26,875 --> 00:20:28,833
- I told you to wait at home.
- Spareribs.

257
00:20:29,625 --> 00:20:30,958
Pork roll.

258
00:20:31,958 --> 00:20:33,375
Fried chicken.

259
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:36,000
Spareribs.

260
00:20:36,708 --> 00:20:37,625
Pork roll.

261
00:20:38,125 --> 00:20:39,625
[tense music playing]

262
00:20:39,708 --> 00:20:42,500
Fried chi-- [groans]

263
00:20:42,583 --> 00:20:44,583
[dramatic music playing]

264
00:20:45,083 --> 00:20:46,916
Hey. I was buying dinner.

265
00:20:47,500 --> 00:20:48,708
Why am I here?

266
00:21:18,583 --> 00:21:19,500
Han?

267
00:21:20,958 --> 00:21:23,875
- Why am I back here?
- [grandma 2] What's going on?

268
00:21:23,958 --> 00:21:27,083
Did your conscience get the better of you?
Is that why?

269
00:21:27,166 --> 00:21:28,750
- They were possessed.
- Oh.

270
00:21:30,041 --> 00:21:31,541
It's Tien-chi's doing.

271
00:21:32,791 --> 00:21:34,291
What's he playing at?

272
00:21:35,625 --> 00:21:39,416
- Should they stay here with us or what?
- [thunder cracking]

273
00:21:40,458 --> 00:21:42,083
[Han Chieh] It's almost dark.

274
00:21:43,541 --> 00:21:45,541
[suspenseful music playing]

275
00:21:55,041 --> 00:21:57,041
[music intensifies]

276
00:22:12,833 --> 00:22:14,833
[Tien-chi] Come on out, my friends.

277
00:22:20,375 --> 00:22:22,791
[ghosts growl]

278
00:22:22,875 --> 00:22:25,583
Go to Dongfeng Market.

279
00:22:25,666 --> 00:22:29,541
Have fun with that little whiny brat, Han.

280
00:22:29,625 --> 00:22:30,833
This time,

281
00:22:31,875 --> 00:22:36,791
there's no way
they can take my demon powers!

282
00:22:37,375 --> 00:22:39,500
[laughs]

283
00:22:40,500 --> 00:22:41,708
Go now.

284
00:22:49,750 --> 00:22:51,750
[suspenseful music continues]

285
00:23:03,250 --> 00:23:04,541
DONGFENG RESIDENTS ONLY

286
00:23:04,625 --> 00:23:05,875
Watch the steps.

287
00:23:07,833 --> 00:23:09,416
- Drink some water.
- Here you go.

288
00:23:09,500 --> 00:23:11,500
[somber music playing]

289
00:23:18,583 --> 00:23:19,416
Hey, Han.

290
00:23:20,666 --> 00:23:23,666
What do you think is happening?
Is the Demon King coming?

291
00:23:26,083 --> 00:23:27,291
Not long now.

292
00:23:27,833 --> 00:23:29,500
He's waiting for the full moon.

293
00:23:30,916 --> 00:23:34,333
This war, it will last all night.
You ready?

294
00:23:34,416 --> 00:23:37,083
Hey, you and I, we're together.

295
00:23:37,166 --> 00:23:39,375
I can last as long as you can.

296
00:23:41,041 --> 00:23:44,375
- Do you have a knife?
- A knife? What use is that?

297
00:23:44,875 --> 00:23:45,750
You'll see.

298
00:23:46,708 --> 00:23:48,541
I only have a few pogs left.

299
00:23:48,625 --> 00:23:51,583
I need to use these very sparingly.

300
00:23:52,583 --> 00:23:55,125
Put one of the protective talismans
I've given you.

301
00:23:55,208 --> 00:23:57,041
Put it on the knife. It'll help.

302
00:23:57,125 --> 00:23:58,666
[low action music playing]

303
00:23:58,750 --> 00:24:01,291
Yeh Tzu. Ms. Lo. Mei-na.

304
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:05,625
Gather all the neighbors' keys here,

305
00:24:05,708 --> 00:24:08,416
and start stockpiling supplies
just in case.

306
00:24:08,500 --> 00:24:10,500
We're getting ready for a war.

307
00:24:13,791 --> 00:24:15,791
[music fades]

308
00:24:15,875 --> 00:24:17,208
[thunder rumbling]

309
00:24:29,333 --> 00:24:31,333
[mysterious music playing]

310
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:43,791
We're fighting a war,
so why are you bringing all this?

311
00:24:43,875 --> 00:24:45,875
Mr. Han! Mr. Han!

312
00:24:46,666 --> 00:24:48,250
I think something's over there.

313
00:25:02,166 --> 00:25:03,833
[suspenseful music playing]

314
00:25:03,916 --> 00:25:05,791
[growls]

315
00:25:19,333 --> 00:25:20,208
[roars]

316
00:26:41,583 --> 00:26:43,583
[suspenseful music continues]

317
00:26:49,750 --> 00:26:50,875
[roars]

318
00:26:59,458 --> 00:27:01,458
- [music stops]
- [gunshots]

319
00:27:03,375 --> 00:27:05,375
[action music playing]

320
00:27:15,375 --> 00:27:17,458
- What is that?
- The gun of kindness.

321
00:27:17,541 --> 00:27:21,166
Hope it helps.
Lord Guan has blessed our bullets.

322
00:27:21,250 --> 00:27:23,125
Why aren't you using your pogs?

323
00:27:23,208 --> 00:27:24,583
I intend to.

324
00:27:33,166 --> 00:27:35,166
[music builds]

325
00:27:37,416 --> 00:27:39,375
[growling]

326
00:27:58,666 --> 00:27:59,958
Go away.

327
00:28:03,375 --> 00:28:05,375
[suspenseful music playing]

328
00:28:13,250 --> 00:28:15,166
[A-Fu] Why are they leaving?
They're all going.

329
00:28:15,250 --> 00:28:18,833
- [man knocking] Ms. Wang. Open the door.
- [Ms. Lo] What's happening?

330
00:28:19,458 --> 00:28:20,708
Open the door, please.

331
00:28:20,791 --> 00:28:23,166
DEMON KING OF THE SIXTH HEAVEN
IS NOT ALLOWED IN OR HE'LL DIE

332
00:28:29,125 --> 00:28:31,041
- [growls]
- [screams]

333
00:28:31,125 --> 00:28:32,958
No, no, no! Shut the gate!

334
00:28:33,458 --> 00:28:35,000
[suspenseful music playing]

335
00:28:38,083 --> 00:28:40,083
- [gunshots]
- [action music playing]

336
00:28:57,041 --> 00:28:59,708
- [music fades]
- [sinister whistling]

337
00:29:31,208 --> 00:29:33,208
[suspenseful music intensifies]

338
00:30:01,166 --> 00:30:04,041
They're all coming now. You guys go inside
and protect all the others.

339
00:30:04,125 --> 00:30:05,833
I'm glad A-Fu taught us this.

340
00:30:06,416 --> 00:30:10,625
Mr. Han. My heart won't stop pounding.
We're so scared.

341
00:30:11,458 --> 00:30:13,458
[somber music playing]

342
00:30:17,666 --> 00:30:18,500
Yeh Tzu.

343
00:30:19,333 --> 00:30:20,291
Not here.

344
00:30:24,958 --> 00:30:26,083
[Han] Look after things here.

345
00:30:27,416 --> 00:30:28,250
[door closes]

346
00:30:31,041 --> 00:30:32,333
Did you see Yeh Tzu?

347
00:30:32,833 --> 00:30:34,375
Isn't she with you?

348
00:30:34,458 --> 00:30:35,458
[sighs]

349
00:30:37,750 --> 00:30:39,708
[somber music continues]

350
00:30:40,208 --> 00:30:41,458
[ghost] Ground floor.

351
00:30:47,583 --> 00:30:48,833
We'd better get in.

352
00:31:13,250 --> 00:31:14,958
[dramatic music playing]

353
00:31:16,958 --> 00:31:19,458
- [Han Chieh] Tien-chi.
- Duh, duh, duh…

354
00:31:30,875 --> 00:31:31,958
[music intensifies]

355
00:31:34,291 --> 00:31:35,333
[chuckles softly]

356
00:31:36,750 --> 00:31:39,333
You really thought
the red and white ghosts were in her house

357
00:31:39,416 --> 00:31:42,666
because her mom hired
that lousy feng shui master?

358
00:31:47,166 --> 00:31:49,250
Hello, Master Han. I'm Yeh Tzu.

359
00:31:49,333 --> 00:31:51,666
This was placed under my father's pillow.

360
00:31:51,750 --> 00:31:53,333
The ghost was a woman.

361
00:31:53,416 --> 00:31:55,250
[eerie music playing]

362
00:31:57,666 --> 00:32:00,166
From the very beginning,

363
00:32:00,250 --> 00:32:03,375
she's been a pawn
the Demon King placed beside you.

364
00:32:05,458 --> 00:32:08,916
I made the red and white ghosts
visit her house every night,

365
00:32:09,875 --> 00:32:13,791
to pass my demonic energy into her body.

366
00:32:14,791 --> 00:32:17,416
She's been growing a liver
for the Demon King.

367
00:32:25,875 --> 00:32:28,208
[Tien-chi] Long time no see.

368
00:32:45,958 --> 00:32:49,166
You have become more mature than you were.

369
00:32:50,666 --> 00:32:51,833
[eerie music continues]

370
00:32:51,916 --> 00:32:53,416
My fists are stronger now.

371
00:32:54,000 --> 00:32:54,958
Want to test it?

372
00:32:56,416 --> 00:32:57,458
Hmm.

373
00:32:59,791 --> 00:33:03,666
The feel of your fist on my face

374
00:33:04,625 --> 00:33:09,125
will give me more satisfaction
than any other agent from above…

375
00:33:10,083 --> 00:33:11,208
ever has.

376
00:33:11,791 --> 00:33:13,208
Stop all this bullshit.

377
00:33:13,791 --> 00:33:16,666
You used Chi-sha and Yeh Tzu,

378
00:33:17,166 --> 00:33:18,625
to train a new assistant,

379
00:33:19,375 --> 00:33:20,458
Tien-chi, right?

380
00:33:21,125 --> 00:33:23,000
Wu Tien-chi? Hmm.

381
00:33:23,583 --> 00:33:26,791
He's evil enough.
It's a shame he's not talented though.

382
00:33:26,875 --> 00:33:30,333
Don't you think it's a waste to give him
a treasure like a demonic liver?

383
00:33:33,083 --> 00:33:34,375
[eerie music continues]

384
00:33:36,500 --> 00:33:37,333
[exhales]

385
00:33:37,416 --> 00:33:39,125
My liver belongs to you.

386
00:33:41,208 --> 00:33:42,041
Really?

387
00:33:42,125 --> 00:33:45,375
Stronger than Wu Tien-chi,
and younger than Chen Chi-sha.

388
00:33:45,458 --> 00:33:47,416
You're the best choice.

389
00:33:50,583 --> 00:33:55,625
I'm so jealous of the Third Crown Prince.
How could he find such a good assistant?

390
00:33:56,666 --> 00:33:58,041
Come work with me.

391
00:33:58,708 --> 00:34:01,458
I won't treat you badly
like the Third Crown Prince.

392
00:34:01,541 --> 00:34:03,833
I can give you anything you desire.

393
00:34:03,916 --> 00:34:07,458
You can beat up and kill anyone you want.

394
00:34:11,583 --> 00:34:13,333
Beating you up is better.

395
00:34:14,166 --> 00:34:16,208
I don't want to eat your shit.

396
00:34:16,291 --> 00:34:18,625
Oh. So you only kill bad guys.

397
00:34:18,708 --> 00:34:20,041
Is that right?

398
00:34:20,541 --> 00:34:23,166
Hmm. But wait.

399
00:34:24,416 --> 00:34:27,083
You killed your whole family.

400
00:34:28,708 --> 00:34:32,416
You're evil and you deserve to die.

401
00:34:33,083 --> 00:34:35,833
That's why I'm indebted
to the Crown Prince.

402
00:34:36,333 --> 00:34:39,791
[laughing] You know…

403
00:34:40,500 --> 00:34:43,750
if you let me transplant
the liver into you,

404
00:34:44,250 --> 00:34:46,791
you will have such enormous power,

405
00:34:47,500 --> 00:34:51,291
that you can be completely rid
of the Third Crown Prince.

406
00:34:52,083 --> 00:34:54,541
If you become my agent,

407
00:34:54,625 --> 00:34:57,416
we could conquer
all three realms together.

408
00:34:57,500 --> 00:34:59,375
Fuck you, you bastard.

409
00:34:59,458 --> 00:35:01,458
[tense music playing]

410
00:35:02,333 --> 00:35:04,583
You think I'll let you have a choice?

411
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:09,958
It's too late. My liver has grown large.

412
00:35:10,041 --> 00:35:14,333
It could burst out of her at any time,
and tear her body to pieces.

413
00:35:18,375 --> 00:35:21,583
Will you let that happen to her? Hmm?

414
00:35:32,208 --> 00:35:33,041
Okay.

415
00:35:33,875 --> 00:35:35,541
But there's two conditions.

416
00:35:36,458 --> 00:35:38,708
Spare everyone here in the market.

417
00:35:39,708 --> 00:35:40,583
And…

418
00:35:44,333 --> 00:35:45,750
I want her to live.

419
00:35:45,833 --> 00:35:47,458
[music turns sad]

420
00:35:48,208 --> 00:35:49,583
Give her my liver.

421
00:35:53,958 --> 00:35:57,041
But she's been doomed to die,
didn't you know?

422
00:35:59,250 --> 00:36:00,458
What are you saying?

423
00:36:01,333 --> 00:36:04,791
The leukemia has almost
already destroyed her.

424
00:36:05,500 --> 00:36:06,958
This entire time,

425
00:36:07,041 --> 00:36:11,000
she's only been kept alive
by the power of the demonic liver.

426
00:36:13,958 --> 00:36:15,958
Oh. Didn't she tell you?

427
00:36:16,041 --> 00:36:17,791
[laughing]

428
00:36:21,083 --> 00:36:24,875
[Yeh Tzu] <i>After I got sick, I'd sometimes</i>
<i>come and have quiet time here.</i>

429
00:36:24,958 --> 00:36:28,541
[Han] <i>You really believe</i>
<i>the world will become peaceful?</i>

430
00:36:28,625 --> 00:36:29,666
It might.

431
00:36:29,750 --> 00:36:31,583
Hey, smile!

432
00:36:32,666 --> 00:36:35,833
[Yeh Tzu] <i>Because in there is all my love.</i>

433
00:36:35,916 --> 00:36:37,625
[sad music continues]

434
00:36:41,375 --> 00:36:42,958
Just live an extra day.

435
00:36:47,041 --> 00:36:49,333
Yes. I agree.

436
00:36:49,416 --> 00:36:51,416
[intriguing music playing]

437
00:36:53,833 --> 00:36:55,625
You must give her my liver.

438
00:36:56,750 --> 00:36:58,875
And I must confirm she's alive

439
00:36:59,666 --> 00:37:01,458
before your liver's in my body.

440
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:06,250
Mmm.

441
00:37:06,333 --> 00:37:08,375
I've killed so many people.

442
00:37:09,708 --> 00:37:11,833
It's my first time saving one.

443
00:37:11,916 --> 00:37:13,583
[suspenseful music playing]

444
00:37:15,125 --> 00:37:16,958
Once you come to work for me,

445
00:37:17,041 --> 00:37:19,500
never speak to me in this way again.

446
00:37:22,125 --> 00:37:24,083
[groans]

447
00:37:25,166 --> 00:37:26,375
[music stops]

448
00:37:28,166 --> 00:37:30,166
[theme music playing]

449
00:38:28,166 --> 00:38:30,166
[music continues]

450
00:39:26,583 --> 00:39:28,583
[music continues]

451
00:40:30,375 --> 00:40:32,375
[music continues]

452
00:42:22,666 --> 00:42:24,666
[music ends]
